1) Run : npm init
2) Enter! Enter! Enter!
3) Go to package.json and change   "main": "index.js" to "main" : "app.js"
4) Install express: Run "npm install express"
5) Install mongodb: Run "npm install mongodb"
6) Install mongoose: Run "npm install mongoose"
7) Install nodemon: Run "sudo npm install -g nodemon --save-dev"
8) Go to package.json and add "start":"nodemon app.js": like this
    "scripts": {
                  "start": "nodemon app.js",
                  "test": "echo \"Error: no test specified\" && exit 1"
                },
9) Create app.js in the root folder, enjoy your work